[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Finding S2: Tool-Call Ledger and Booking-Event Journal Accumulate Per-Action Content with Potentially-PHI-Rich Reason-for-Visit Outside Archive-Reference Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Severity:** HIGH
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Expert:** Security (PHI minimization, working-store-vs-archive-store discipline, per-store classification, retention reconciliation)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Location:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Step 4D `audit_tool_call(... arguments: parameters ...)` writes the slot_search arguments which include `parameters.reason_for_visit` (the patient's natural-language reason-for-visit, potentially containing PHI such as condition mentions, medication mentions, or symptom descriptions).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Step 6D pseudocode `booking_event_journal.write({... notes: session.search_parameters.reason_for_visit ...})` writes the patient's natural-language reason-for-visit into the durable journal record under Object-Lock-in-compliance-mode for the regulatory-retention window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Step 3D `audit_tool_call(tool: "patient_lookup", arguments: redact_sensitive(identifiers), ...)` correctly redacts identifiers (good, partial credit).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Step 10A `redact_user_phi(turn)` and `redact_sensitive_args(call)` are named at conversation close but the tool-call ledger and booking-event journal records have already been written at the time of the action with the unredacted content; the close-time redaction does not flow back to the already-written records.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Cross-Cutting Design Points "The booking is durable; the conversation is not" paragraph: "The bot's job after booking is to confirm successfully and make sure the patient understands what was booked; the bot is not the appointment's home." The architecture correctly elevates the durable-record-versus-conversation distinction but does not specify the per-store working-store discipline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Problem:** Same chapter pattern as 10.1-10.10 and 11.1's working-store discipline, with recipe-distinct booking-event-journal-as-durable-record amplification. Recipe-acute and recipe-distinct because:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The booking-event journal is the recipe's load-bearing durable-record artifact.** The journal is written under Object-Lock-in-compliance-mode for the regulatory-retention window, which by design prevents modification or deletion within the retention window. Writing the patient's natural-language reason-for-visit ("notes: session.search_parameters.reason_for_visit") into this durable record commits a potentially-PHI-rich free-text field to the durable archive without the redaction discipline the audit pipeline applies at conversation close. The reason-for-visit may include clinical conditions ("biopsy of the suspicious mass on my left breast"), medication mentions ("follow-up after my chemotherapy"), symptom descriptions ("the chest pain is back"), social-history details ("after I lost my job and my insurance"), or family-member context ("my husband had a similar episode"). Each of these is PHI by association and benefits from the redaction-or-structured-extraction discipline rather than the free-text-archive discipline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The tool-call ledger writes per-action arguments at the time of the action, not at conversation close.** The Step 4D audit_tool_call entry includes `arguments: parameters` (where `parameters` is the structured search parameters including the patient's natural-language reason-for-visit). The Step 5B audit_tool_call entry for slot_hold includes only structural identifiers (`slot_id`); the Step 6B audit_tool_call entry for slot_book includes only structural identifiers (`hold_id, slot_id`); these are correct. The Step 4D entry is the one that commits potentially-PHI-rich content to the ledger. The Step 10A close-time `redact_sensitive_args(call)` references this redaction but the architecture does not specify whether the close-time redaction overwrites the already-written ledger entries or only flows into the conversation-close audit_record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   3. **The recipe's `notes: session.search_parameters.reason_for_visit` write to the booking-event journal is the recipe-distinct architectural choice.** The institution's scheduling system also receives the reason-for-visit (typically as a structured field or a free-text note); the bot's booking-event journal is duplicating this content into the bot's audit pipeline. The architecture should specify whether this duplication is necessary (the scheduling system's record is the source of truth for the appointment; the bot's booking-event journal is the source of truth for the bot's role in the booking; the reason-for-visit may belong only in the scheduling system's record), or whether the journal should record only the structural booking metadata (confirmation_id, patient_id_hash, slot_id, provider, location, visit_type, appointment_time, booking_initiated_through, session_id, booked_at) with the reason-for-visit referenced via a pointer to the conversation log or the scheduling system's record rather than embedded inline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The DynamoDB tool-call-ledger table is on the real-time hot path during the encounter.** The ledger is written on every tool invocation and read at conversation close for the audit_record assembly. The wider the per-row content surface, the wider the real-time access surface for biometric-derived and PHI-rich content. The Step 4D `parameters` write commits the patient's natural-language reason-for-visit to the hot-path table for the duration of the encounter and beyond.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The minimum-necessary requirement is at risk on the hot path.** The tool-call ledger's purpose during the encounter is to hold the structural reference to each tool call (tool name, invocation timestamp, structural arguments, structural result, latency, outcome). The free-text reason-for-visit, the patient identifiers, and the per-call arguments that include PHI are not necessary on the real-time hot path; the audit pipeline (Step 10A audit_record at conversation close, archived via Firehose) is the durable archive surface, the tool-call-ledger should hold only structural references on the hot path.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   6. **The booking-event journal's retention regime is recipe-distinct.** Object-Lock-in-compliance-mode for the regulatory-retention window aligns with the audit pipeline's retention; the booking-event journal also has medical-records retention obligations that may be longer than the audit-pipeline retention floor (per-state medical-records retention rules vary; some are longer than HIPAA's six-year minimum). The architecture should specify the per-record-class retention reconciliation with the explicit per-state floor enumeration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   7. **The per-record access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer; the booking-event journal's access-control surface is the practice operations team plus the audit-and-compliance team plus the patient-rights handlers; the conversation log's access-control surface is narrower; the tool-call ledger's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. The architecture should specify the per-record-class access-control matrix.
