[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The patient receives the response immediately and acts on it.** Unlike the FAQ bot's information-only responses, the scheduling bot's responses include actionable claims about the patient's account: "your appointment is booked for Tuesday May 28 at 7:30 AM with Dr. Patel," "your appointment was canceled and you'll receive a confirmation," "Dr. Patel has openings on Tuesday and Thursday." Each of these is a claim the patient acts on; an LLM that hallucinates content (a slot that the slot_search tool did not return; a confirmation that the slot_book tool did not produce; a cancellation that the slot_cancel tool did not execute) produces patient-facing communication that the patient cannot verify and that the institution may not catch until the patient shows up for an appointment that does not exist.
