[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The recipe-distinct tool-call-injection threat is recipe-acute.** A successful prompt-injection on a tool-using-LLM is more consequential than on a generation-only LLM: a malicious utterance that triggers the agent to call slot_book with manipulated arguments (a different patient_id, a different slot, a different visit-type) produces a real-world action against the institution's scheduling system. The recipe correctly creates the audit trail of every tool call (Step 10A `tool_calls: [...]` in the audit_record) but the tool-call-history audits what was called, not whether the call was the right call given the patient's intent.
