[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The four expert lenses produce overlapping concerns at four intersections.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conversation-log-and-tool-call-ledger-and-booking-event-journal-as-PHI-by-association governance (Security S1) overlaps with the working-store discipline (Security S2), the LLM faithfulness check (Security S3), the prompt-injection mitigation (Security S4), the per-cohort monitoring (Architecture A1), and the per-channel authentication (Networking N1).** The Security expert's conversation-log-and-booking-event-journal governance framing with the recipe-distinct authenticated-portal-vs-unauthenticated-channel-and-transactional-action-as-disclosure-event-and-booking-event-journal-as-separate-compliance-record-class amplifications is operationally connected to the working-store discipline (the tool-call-ledger-as-archive-reference and booking-event-journal-as-structural-record patterns naturally support the per-record-class retention reconciliation, the deletion-propagation, and the disclosure-accounting log integration), to the LLM faithfulness check (the per-claim citation-grounding-to-tool-results discipline supports the audit-record-reproducibility per Finding A4; the faithfulness-failure-rate is part of the per-cohort metrics per Finding A1), to the prompt-injection mitigation (the input-screening PHI redaction operates alongside the input-screening prompt-injection detection; the per-language jailbreak-test corpus discipline integrates with the per-language redaction-taxonomy per Finding A7), to the per-cohort monitoring (per-cohort patient-rights workflow ensures that per-cohort metrics do not become a de-anonymization vector), and to the per-channel authentication (the per-channel session-token discipline is the input-side of the conversation-log governance scaffolding). The six findings reinforce each other; the consolidated fix specifies the conversation-log-and-tool-call-ledger-and-booking-event-journal governance as the architectural primitive with the per-cohort monitoring, the faithfulness check, the prompt-injection mitigation, and the per-channel authentication threading through the same per-channel-and-per-classification mechanism.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    810[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    811[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring (Architecture A1) overlaps with the tool-surface contract management (Architecture A2), the identity-verification policy (Architecture A3), the foundation-model-and-prompt versioning (Architecture A4), the multi-language deployment (Architecture A7), and the accessibility (Architecture A11).** Per-language deployment is an explicit cohort axis; per-language launch-gate per Finding A1 reinforces per-language asset-development per Finding A7. Per-cohort identity-verification-friction-as-equity-metric reinforces per-policy-version identity-verification-policy-as-versioned-governance-artifact per Finding A3. Per-tool failure rates per Finding A1 reinforce per-tool versioning per Finding A2. Accessibility cohorts (screen-reader users, keyboard-navigation users, voice-input users via the Variations voice-channel extension) are equity-acute per-cohort populations that benefit from the same launch-gate discipline. The five findings reinforce each other and the consolidated fix specifies per-cohort, per-language, per-policy-version, per-tool-version, and per-accessibility-affordance as multi-axis cohort dimensions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    812[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    813[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Slot-hold transactional-contract (Architecture A5) overlaps with the booking-event-journal as separate compliance record (Security S1) and the cross-channel slot-inventory consistency (Architecture A12).** The slot-hold transactional contract is the recipe's load-bearing concurrency-prevention primitive; the cross-channel slot-inventory consistency is the institutional discipline that ensures all booking channels participate in the same hold-and-confirm protocol. The booking-event journal is the durable record of every booking, reschedule, and cancellation; the per-cohort slot-hold-but-not-confirmed-rate metric per Finding A1 surfaces operational issues with the transactional contract.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    814[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    815[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Compensation operations (Architecture A6) overlaps with the patient-rights workflow (Security S1), the booking-event-journal-as-separate-compliance-record-class (Security S1), and the per-cohort monitoring (Architecture A1).** The compensation operation tools (view-booking-history, reverse-booking-with-reason, rebook-with-correct-parameters) integrate with the patient-rights workflow (a patient who reports a wrong appointment requires the compensation tooling to reverse the booking with reason); the booking-event journal preserves the audit trail of the original booking and the compensation events; the per-cohort compensation-event-rate metric is the recipe-distinct equity-acute metric.
