[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    869[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Recipe 11.2 is publishable at the simple-medium-tier level once the three HIGH findings are closed. The Honest Take is the recipe's strongest single passage and the chapter's strongest single articulation of the bot-surfaces-institutional-questions-the-institution-has-avoided primitive in transactional-bot context. The "the scheduling bot is the right second recipe in this chapter, after the FAQ bot, because it is the recipe where the patient-experience improvement is most visible (Marcus's twenty-two-minute phone call versus his ninety-second chat), the operational savings are most measurable, and the operational practices it builds carry forward into every later transactional bot in this chapter" framing matches the chapter pattern from 11.1 while elevating the recipe-distinct visit-type-catalog-as-the-institution's-hardest-hidden-complexity, EHR-integration-most-underestimated, identity-verification-graduated-by-intent-and-channel, slot-hold-as-safety-net-for-concurrency, tool-surface-as-contract-with-versioned-schemas, compensation-as-first-class-operation, booking-claim-verification-as-output-screening, no-show-and-reminder-as-integration-not-feature, per-cohort-identity-verification-success-rate-as-equity-metric, and ninety-second-chat-versus-twenty-two-minute-call patient-experience contributions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    870[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    871[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe's deferral to recipe 11.1 for the chapter-pattern conversation-AI primitives is a defensible composition choice. The recipe's distinct contributions are recipe-distinct and correctly elevated. The Bedrock-Agents-as-tool-orchestration substrate framing with the custom-Lambda-orchestrator-as-flexibility-tradeoff alternative is the architecturally-correct managed-offering composition; the Bedrock-Knowledge-Bases-as-managed-RAG and Guardrails-as-defense-in-depth scope-and-content filtering carries forward from 11.1 with the recipe-distinct narrower-scope-than-FAQ-bot framing; the Lambda-and-API-Gateway-and-WAF-and-DynamoDB-and-S3-and-KMS-and-Secrets-Manager-and-CloudWatch-and-CloudTrail-and-EventBridge-and-Kinesis-Firehose-and-Glue-and-Athena substrate is operationally accurate; the optional-Lex-V2-and-optional-Connect-and-optional-Comprehend-Medical framing is the architecturally-correct optionality.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    872[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    873[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The chapter-wide consolidation work (transactional-bot chapter preface that consolidates the Chapter 11 transactional recipes' tool-surface-and-identity-verification-and-slot-hold-and-compensation discipline into a single chapter-pattern primitive with recipe-distinct amplifications, conversation-log-and-tool-call-ledger-and-booking-event-journal-as-PHI-by-association chapter preface, per-cohort-monitoring-as-launch-gate chapter preface, LLM-clinical-administrative-safety-substrate chapter preface, foundation-model-versioning chapter preface, multi-language chapter preface, disaster-recovery-with-critical-dependency-handling chapter preface, accessibility-as-launch-gate chapter preface, audit-log retention floor chapter preface with per-state and per-channel and per-record-class dimensions, build-vs-buy chapter preface) is deferred to the chapter editor for the next pass.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    874[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    875[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe-specific contributions that should be elevated to the chapter preface as load-bearing primitives are: (a) the **tool-surface-as-contract-with-versioned-schemas primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe; the tool surface is the bot's contract with the institutional system and changes to the tool surface go through documented change management); (b) the **identity-verification-graduated-by-intent-and-channel primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe; the assurance level required for higher-risk actions is correspondingly higher); (c) the **slot-hold-as-safety-net-for-concurrency primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe with multi-channel concurrency concerns; the search-then-hold-then-confirm-then-book pattern is the safety net that prevents double-bookings); (d) the **visit-type-mapping-as-managed-asset primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe with institutional taxonomy that the LLM maps natural-language input to); (e) the **transactional-fulfillment-with-explicit-confirmation primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe; the explicit confirmation step before the action is the architecturally-correct safety primitive); (f) the **compensation-as-first-class-operation primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe; when the bot takes an action that turns out to be wrong, the operational team needs to be able to undo and redo cleanly while preserving the audit trail); (g) the **booking-claim-verification-as-output-screening primitive** (recipe-distinct extension of 11.1's hallucination-check primitive for transactional bots; load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe where the bot's response includes actionable claims about the patient's account); (h) the **no-show-and-reminder-workflows-as-integrations-not-features primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe; the bot integrates with the institution's existing workflows rather than re-implementing them); (i) the **booking-event-journal-as-separate-compliance-record-class primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe with durable-record obligations; the journal is part of the institution's clinical-administrative record with retention and access-control profile distinct from the audit pipeline); (j) the **per-cohort-identity-verification-success-rate-as-equity-metric primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe with identity verification; identity-verification friction disproportionately affects elderly and technologically-less-comfortable patients and is an equity-acute metric); (k) the **bot-surfaces-institutional-questions-the-institution-has-avoided primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any transactional conversational AI recipe deployment; the project surfaces ownership questions about institutional taxonomies, system-of-record decisions, policy consistency that the institution had previously avoided).
